<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,596,765]" pageId="4" pageNumber="419">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="Hubner" box="[272,361,596,621]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,361,596,621]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="419">Melittia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the following characters: Veins R4 and R5 stalked of forewing; Cu1 arising well before crossvein of hindwing; hind tibia and tarsus strongly tufted. Male genitalia: valve usually ovoid, elongate, dorsoapical and ventroapicaI part densely covered with simple hairs; tegumen and uncus broad, uncus bilobed apically; saccus and aedeagus relatively long. Female genitalia: antrum short with annular sclerotization; ductus bursae long; corpus bursae with complicated signum.
</paragraph>
